Political allies of Minister of Interior, Rauf Aregbesola, ex-Speaker, Osun House of Assembly, Najeem Salam and Senator Mudashiru Hussein have declared their support for the candidate of All Progressives Congress(APC), Adegboyega Oyetola ahead of July 16th, 2022 governorship election. The duo who held a meeting with supporters at Gaa Hall, Ejigbo, Osun State on Friday, insisted that APC is their party and they will not leave it at this critical time.   Sallah: Remain steadfast in prayers for peace – Gombe…     Eid-El-Kabir: Only peace, oneness can ensure stability of…     Eid-el-Kabir: APC chieftain urges Nigerians to reflect on…   Speaking with newsmen after the meeting, Salam said, “As 2022 Osun election is drawing close, there is a need to sensitise our people on the need for them to troop out and vote for our party, APC. By virtue of my membership of the party, there is no doubt of where I and my supporters will vote on the election other than APC. I will vote for my party. Wherever I am going is where my supporters are going as far as Osun 2022 governorship election is concerned. Adegboyega Oyetola is an APC member and candidate of the party, so we will support our party.” Speaking about reconciliation ahead of the poll, Salam said, “I listened to the comment of His Excellency on television a few days ago and he talked about the efforts been made to reconcile with those that are not on the same page with him to support the party. Reconciliation with the governor is still ongoing as to end all these crises within our party. It is not a new thing that we are always winning the state. I am always confident that APC will win the 2022 governorship election. It will be a repeat of winning.” Speaking on the issue, Hussein stressed that the candidate of PDP, Senator Ademola Adeleke, is not a threat to the victory of APC in the forthcoming governorship election.